# Quality Ratchet & Drift Detection (R1-Q1, R1-Q9)

## Quality Ratchet (P1-10)

The system remembers how well it has performed and refuses regression.

```python
effective_threshold = max(7.0, rolling_5batch_avg - 0.5)
```

Progression example:
```
Batch 1: avg 7.2 → threshold = 7.0 (floor)
Batch 5: avg 8.1 → threshold = max(7.0, 7.72 - 0.5) = 7.22
Batch 6: avg 8.3 → threshold = max(7.0, 7.92 - 0.5) = 7.42
Batch N: avg 9.0 → threshold ~8.0 (refuses regression)
```

- `iterate/quality_ratchet.py` owns this logic (P1-10)
- The 0.5 buffer prevents one exceptional batch from making threshold unreachable
- The 7.0 floor is immutable — never drops below absolute minimum
- Effective threshold plotted over time in quality trend visualization

## Dimension Floor Constraints

Hard minimums that override aggregate score:

| Dimension | Floor | Effect |
|-----------|-------|--------|
| Clarity | 6.0 | Confusing ad is never publishable |
| Brand Voice | 5.0 | Must sound recognizably like Varsity Tutors |

Floor breach = automatic rejection regardless of weighted average.

## SPC Drift Detection (P2-04)

Statistical Process Control monitors evaluator consistency:

```
Batch scores → Control chart (rolling mean ± 2σ)
                  │
                  ├── Within limits → Continue (no action)
                  │
                  └── Breach → Inject 3-5 canary ads
                                  │
                                  ├── Canary scores normal → Real quality shift
                                  │                          (ratchet adjusts)
                                  │
                                  └── Canary scores drifted → Evaluator drift
                                                               (recalibrate)
```

- `evaluate/drift_detection.py` owns SPC logic (P2-04)
- Control limits: ±2σ from rolling 5-batch mean
- Canary injection only fires when drift is detected — no wasted tokens
- Recalibration uses golden set anchor ads (P0-07)

## Calibration Anchors (P0-06, P0-07)

- **Cold-start calibration:** Run evaluator on 20–30 competitor + reference ads before generating anything
- **Golden set:** 15–20 ads with human-assigned scores across all 5 dimensions
- **Regression gate:** Evaluator must score within ±1.0 of human labels on ≥80% of golden set

## Do NOT

- Modify the 7.0 absolute floor — it's immutable
- Skip floor constraint checks even when aggregate passes
- Ignore SPC breaches — always investigate with canary injection
- Use the same canary ads repeatedly without rotating them
- Calibrate the evaluator against its own generated output (circular)
